<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Responsive Single-Column Layout</title>
    <style>
        /* 1. Reset & Base Styles */
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            
            /* Keeps the footer pushed to the bottom if content is short */
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        /* 2. Layout Containers */
        header, footer {
            background-color: #1a1a1a;
            color: #ffffff;
            padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* The central single column wrapper */
        .container {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 800px; /* Restricts width on large screens for ideal readability */
            margin: 0 auto;   /* Centers the column horizontally */
            padding: 0 1.5rem; /* Prevents text from hitting screen edges on mobile */
        }

        main {
            flex: 1; /* Grows to fill available vertical space */
            padding: 3rem 0;
        }

        /* 3. Typography & Elements */
        header h1 {
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        nav a {
            color: #00bcd4;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin: 0 0.75rem;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        nav a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        article h2 {
            font-size: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: #1a1a1a;
        }

        article p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .hero-image {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            background-color: #ddd; /* Placeholder color */
            aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            color: #666;
        }

        footer p {
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            opacity: 0.8;
        }

        /* 4. Responsive Adjustments */
        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            main {
                padding: 1.5rem 0;
            }
            article h2 {
                font-size: 1.6rem;
            }
            article p {
                font-size: 1rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Header Section -->
    <header>
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="text-center" style="  text-align: center;">Apex Wx</h1>
        <h2 class="text-center" style="   text-align: center;">Fort Kent &amp;
          the Saint John Valley, Maine<br>
          Weather Information</h2>
        <p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maine" title="Flag of Maine -- Click for more"><img
              alt="Maine State Flag" class="img-center" src="https://apexwx.github.io/me.png"
              style="width: 132px; height: 88px; left: 5px; right: 5px; padding: 5px;"
              height="88" width="132"></a><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acadia"
            title="Flag of Acadia -- Click for more"><img alt="Flag of Acadia" class="img-center"
              src="https://apexwx.github.io/Flag_of_Acadia.svg.png" style="width: 132px; height: 87.9px; padding: 5px;"
              width="132"></a></p>
        <nav> <span style="font-size: 12px;">Weather information for Fort Kent
            &amp; the Saint John Valley since 2009</span><br>
          <span style="font-size: 12px;">Member <a href="https://madis.ncep.noaa.gov/snow_project.shtml">APRSWXNET/CWOP</a>
            &amp; <a href="https://weather.gladstonefamily.net/site/E0429">CWOP
            </a>Programs</span><br>
          <br>
          <a href="#home">Home</a> <a href="#articles">Articles</a> <a href="#about">About</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>
    <!-- Main Content Column -->
    <main>
      <div class="container">
        <article>
          <div style="text-align: center;"><label id="lblGreetings"><b>Good
                Morning!</b></label></div>
          <div id="localTime" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px; text-align: center;">Saturday,
            May 23, 2026 at 10:21 am EDT</div>
          <div style="font-size: 12px; text-align: center;"><u><strong><br>
              </strong></u></div>
          <div style="text-align: center;"><u> </u></div>
          <div style="font-size: 14px; text-align: center;"><u><strong>Current
                Time (24-Hour)</strong></u> </div>
          <div id="dualTime" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; text-align: center;">10:21
            EDT<br>
            14:21 UTC</div>
          <div style="font-size: 12px; text-align: center;">EST -5 hours / EDT
            -4 hours from UTC</div>
          <div style="font-size: 12px; text-align: center;">Many weather graphic
            timestamps are in UTC / Z Time</div>
          <div style="font-size: 12px; text-align: center;"><br>
          </div>
          <div style="font-size: 12px; text-align: center;"> <a href="https://www.weather.gov/SKYWARN"
              title="NWS Skywarn Storm Spotter" target="_blank"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ApexWx/ApexWx.github.io/master/nws%20skywarn%20storm%20spotter%20logo.jpg"
                alt="NWS Skywarn Storm Spotter" style="width: 124px; height: 72px; max-width: 100%; padding: 5px;"></a><a
              href="https://www.worldcampus.psu.edu/degrees-and-certificates/penn-state-online-weather-forecasting-undergraduate-certificate"
              title="Penn State Certificate in Weather Forecasting" target="_blank"><img
                src="https://github.com/ApexWx/ApexWx.github.io/blob/master/Penn%20State.png?raw=true"
                alt="Penn State Certificate in Weather Forecasting" style="width: 124px; height: 72px; max-width: 100%; padding: 5px;"></a></div>
          <div style="text-align: center;"><br>
            <a href="https://www.buymeacoffee.com/MaineApexWx" target="_blank"><img
                alt="Buy Me A Coffee" src="https://cdn.buymeacoffee.com/buttons/v2/default-yellow.png"
                style="height: 60px !important; width: 217px !important;" height="60"
                width="217"></a><br>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center" style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-size: 12px;">Contributions
              help support this weather information service.</span></div>
          <h2></h2>
          <!-- Placeholder for an image element -->
          <div class="hero-image">
            <h1 class="text-center" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ApexWx/ApexWx.github.io/master/Apex%20banner.jpg"
                alt="Apex Wx Website Banner"></h1>
          </div>
          <p>Single-column layouts are the backbone of modern, mobile-first web
            design. By stripping away cluttered sidebars and complex grid
            systems, you force the reader's focus directly onto the content that
            matters most.</p>
          <p>This approach naturally translates across devices. On a desktop
            screen, a strict <code>max-width</code> constraint ensures that
            line lengths don't stretch too far, preserving ideal typography
            scaling and reading comfort. On mobile devices, the layout
            seamlessly scales down to match the native viewport width without
            requiring heavy media query overhauls.</p>
          <p>Whether you are building a personal blog, a landing page, or a
            documentation portal, starting with a robust single column
            guarantees a clean, accessible foundation.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>
    <!-- Footer Section -->
    <footer>
      <div class="container">
        <p>© 2026 Minimalist Journal. Built with clean semantic HTML &amp; CSS.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
